much more moving and resizing windows on large display; almost no maximising of windows; usually resizing window to 60-70{\%} of screen sufficient ={\textgreater} suggests there is an upper bound of window size that users are comfortable with
- minimising done on single and dual to save screen space, but rarely done on large display

Benefits large display
1. multi-window tasks: interleaving between windows can be reduced
2. rich information tasks: does not have to scroll left/right and up/down in spreadsheet, reduces navigation overhead
3. awareness of peripheral applications: can improve work productivity, able to see to-do lists, email, etc. whereas in smaller screen only primary application window fully visible
4. immersive experience: engaged people more in daily work; felt ‘surrounded' by task

Design recommendations
- legibility (peripheral further from focal attention so increase font size)
- quick switching and moving
- simplified layout
- additional window operations: more likely to move and resize windows on large display; less likely to minimise and maximise},
